Lecture : 5
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-> Hooks

Q - two types of export/import
Default  export/import
export default Component;
Import Component from “path”

Named export/import
export const Component
Import {Component} form “path”


#React Hooks
(Normal JS Utility Function)
- useState() - superpowerful state Variables
- useEffect()

Whenever a state variable update, react re-render the components.

Reconciliation Algorithm (React fiber - react16)
virtual DOM(javaScript object representation) is the representation of actual DOM
Read the Document : acdite link (https://github.com/acdlite/react-fiber-architecture)

Why React is fast?
Ans - Efficient DOM manipulation

Q - Array Destructuring


Lecture : 6
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-> Monolothic VS Microservices
-> Seperation of Convern

Approach 1
App Loads --> API (wait for data tooks 500ms) --> Render (more lagging)

Approach 2
Loads --> Render(website skeleton) --> API (geys data tooks 500ms) --> Re-render (data with less Lagging)


-> useEffect Hooks
---------------------
When the body function will render, useEffect will render it, as soon as it complete render it will call the callback function


for CORS - add the extension in the chrom browser
https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/allow-cors-access-control/lhobafahddgcelffkeicbaginigeejlf?hl=en&pli=1


-> fetch POST call

--> MOCK SERVER
Open postman
0. Create a ne wcollection (react)
1. Add get request with swiggy URL
2. save the response
3. Create Mock SERVER with using "react" as a collection
4. Create new request by appending the swiggy UR after Mock 
    eg (https://c9a29fe6-e559-4e9c-a218-db404f8f049f.mock.pstmn.io/https://namastedev.com/api/v1/listRestaurants)


Shimmer Using, Conditional Rendering
Whenerver there is a change in state variable, react triggers a reconciliation cycle(re-render the component)
--> react-fiber






